A style mixing shiny soft looking skin while also being good at muscle definition.

How to use
Prompt as usual, dataset contains only females but it seems to do males pretty good as well. The sharp linework seems to result in slightly better hands too, at least on AOM2.
The LoRA can be used at anything from 0.5 to 1.0, at lower strength it can be used as an assistance to make cleaner images with sharper lines and at higher you get closer to full RD-RN experience.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

Misc
512 resolution trained on NAI without noise offset option for best LoRA compatibility.
Warning - May contain traces of nuts, a few of the 30 dataset images had futanari content.
All images are untouched raw txt2imgs upscaled, no inpainting done, for quality transparency.

items.name: Sunny of Spades (Stuffy Bunny) - Derpixon Character
items.description:
LoRA for Sunny of Spades (Stuffy Bunny).

This is my last Derpixon character for now, but I don't know if there are people waiting on me to make other characters. Let me know if that's the case and I'll consider it.

I trained it with 72 screencaps I manually took and edited. I trained it at 20 epochs with a dim/alpha of 64/32.

I think it turned out well, but let me know how it goes for you. Read stuff below on guidelines and known issues :)

Triggers:

  • Input "Sunny of Spades, 1girl" after the LoRA near the start of the prompt.

  • Input "pink hair, ponytail" for more consistent face if needed.

  • Input "crop top, jeans, denim" for classic clothes. NB: can place in negative prompts if the clothes are stubbornly appearing.

Notes:

  • My experience has shown scale 0.5 ~ 0.95 work best; my best results were 0.7.

  • My prompt order shown in the sample pictures worked best for me.

  • Works on different models though weights may need to change for good results.

  • I used FoxyaNSFW model and Midnight Maple model, the latter gave best results for this LoRA.

  • Refer to my pictures for examples and what upscaler I used, keep in mind I have used other textual inversions to help with poses and negatives.

  • Backgrounds can be too simple or abract due to image sources, so add "simple background" to negatives if needed.

  • Can take give some strange results sometimes.

  • Closeups work really well but long distances aren't the best.

  • The "heart eyes" she has appear correctly in many "eye focus", "face focus" and "close up" shots but don't if too far away. NB: inputting "heart-shaped pupils" or "symbol-shaped pupils" just confuses the whole thing even more.

I don't think people read entire descriptions like this, but congrats if you do

items.name: Gwendolyn Tennyson (Lucky Girl) - Ben 10
items.description:
LoRA for Gwendolyn Tennyson from Ben 10.

If you like my work and want to support me, please consider supporting me on my Ko-fi page. I'm open to donations and commissions for art and LoRAs with no censorship.

*Refer to version notes for Version 2 of this LoRA and how to use that one

I trained it with 74 pics, which was a mix of mainly fan art and some screencaps. I trained it at 10 epochs with a dim/alpha of 16/8.

Leans to a semi-real look mostly, but somewhat more cartoonish at higher LoRA weights. Let me know how it goes for you. Read stuff below on guidelines and known issues :)

Triggers:

  • Input "Gwendolyn Tennyson, 1girl" after the LoRA near the start of the prompt.

  • Input "orange hair, green eyes" for more consistency if needed, but I didn't find it necessary.

  • Input "long sleeves, white pants" for classic clothes. NB: can place in negative prompts if the clothes are stubbornly appearing.

Notes:

  • My experience has shown scale 0.7 ~ 1 works best; my best results were 0.7 for semi-realistic, but overall favourite was 1.

  • My prompt order shown in the sample pictures worked best for me.

  • Works on different models though weights may need to change for good results.

  • I used Anything4.5 model and Midnight Maple model. Midnight Maple gave best results for this LoRA for me.

  • Refer to my pictures for examples and what upscaler I used, keep in mind I have used other textual inversions to help with poses and negatives.

  • I think this is personally very flexible, at least in terms of changing poses, clothes etc. Other LoRA's and/or Models seem to bring out the more cartoon appearance so experiment for styles.

I don't think people read entire descriptions like this, but congrats if you do

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description:
Lora Update for Gwendolyn Tennyson Alternate Outfits (Ben 10)

If you like my work and want to support me, please consider visiting me on my Ko-fi page. I'm open to donations and commissions for art and LoRAs with no censorship.

This is not meant to replace the previous LoRA. It's merely so that you can get alternative outfits, namely the "Lucky Girl" one. Though, it can still easily produce Gwen pictures with her in different outfits, it won't be able to make pictures of her in her classic blue shirt.

I trained this LoRA with the same dataset as the previous version except I replaced most of the images with Gwen in her classic outfit with ones of her in her "Lucky Girl" outfit. In addition I included a few pictures of her in her green swimsuit, but this focuses on her Lucky Girl look.

Please play around with the LoRA weights. Let me know how it goes for you. Read stuff below on guidelines and known issues :)

Triggers:

  • The global activation tag is "Gwendolyn_Tennyson, 1girl" which is the same as before. Though it will now skew towards giving her the new outfit instead.

  • To get her Lucky Girl outfit you may want to add the prompts below:

mask, necklace, gloves, bodysuit

NB: can place individual items of clothing in the prompts and/or in negative prompts if the clothes are stubbornly not appearing and you don't want them. For example if you put the triggers above and put mask in negatives, you will get her in her Lucky Girl outfit without the mask.

Notes:

  • My experience has shown scale 0.7 ~ 1 works best; my best results were 1.

  • My prompt order shown in the sample pictures worked best for me.

  • Works on different models though weights may need to change for good results.

  • Refer to my pictures for examples and what model and upscaler I used, keep in mind I have used other textual inversions to help with poses and negatives.

You likely won't get a perfect example image of her Lucky Girl outfit, but it should be relatively similar. I noticed that using different models with this drastically changes how different the suit looks so experiment.

items.name: T.M. Opera O (umamusume)
items.description:
LoHa of T.M. Opera O (umamusume). Please install extension on WebUI.

After installing extension, put LoHa file in your sd/models/lora folder and write LoRA notation in prompt to applying LoHa. <lora:loha_name:weight>

All of my works is free. If you'd like to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. 👍

Recommended options

  • LoRA weight 0.7 ~ 0.8

  • Trigger words

    • Base

      • t.m. opera o \(umamusume\)

      • Mini crown and ear piercing are not included!

    • Hair ornament (not necessary for new year costume)

      • mini crown, ear piercing

    • Racing competition costume :

      • mini crown, ear piercing, white shirt, shoulder armor, pink cape, puffy sleeves, long sleeves, jewelry, fingerless gloves, single glove, white gloves, multiple rings, corset, white skirt, pink skirt, two-tone skirt, pleated skirt, white thighhighs, zettai ryouiki, high heel boots, yellow footwear

    • New year:

      • official alternate costume, japanese clothes, kimono, blue jacket, shirt, epaulettes, aiguillette, long sleeves, wide sleeves, white gloves, sash, hakama skirt, obi, floral print, high heel boots

    • Casual

      • ear piercing, white shirt, dress shirt, collared shirt, black jacket, open clothes, open jacket, long sleeves, shirt tucked in, belt, plaid pants

    • Tracen summer uniform

      • tracen school uniform, summer uniform, serafuku, puffy short sleeves, bowtie, horseshoe ornament, sailor collar, sailor shirt, frills, white skirt, purple shirt, miniskirt, zettai ryouiki, white thighhighs, brown footwear, shoes

Use a model derived from or mixed with animefull model.

  • Settings

    • Stable Diffusion WebUI by Automatic1111

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • I recommend kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • Use Hires.fix to get higher quality image

      • Upscaler

        • Latent, Latent (nearest-exact), Latent (bicubic antialiased) or other Latent series.

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss.

    • LyCORIS by KohakuBlueleaf

    • Thank you all a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned model

  • 97 images consist of

    • 4x low quality 35 images

    • 8x medium quality 30 images

    • 16x high quality 32 images

    • => 1 epoch = 892 images

  • replaced character feature tags with t.m. opera o (umamusume)

    • Relation with Uma Musume

      • 1girl, solo, horse girl, horse tail, horse ears, animal ears, tail through clothes,

    • Hair

      • hair over one eye, bangs, brown hair, short hair, orange hair, multicolored hair, blonde hair

    • Eye

      • purple eyes,

    • Unnecessary

      • simple background,

  • I think these tags are

    • the essentials of T.M. Opera O

    • or unnecessary for training because of duplication.

    • t.m. opera o \(umamusume\) contains above tags.

  • resolution : 768x768 with aspect ratio bucketing.

  • other training settings is included in training_data.zip or metadata in LoRA file.

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

And, special thanks to my best friend. DH.

items.name: Kim Kardashian
items.description:
Sometimes, you just build a billionaire's enterprise on a leaked adult tape.

There's some slight redundancy to having a embedding of her, since most models are familiar with her due to her prevalence online. This should provide more consistency however, as SD1.5 amalgamates everything, fanart, old photos, bad pictures, photoshops etc.

The embed has been trained on SD 1.5 and works well on most 1.5 based models. When rendering full body images I recommend using inpainting. It also works well to let the AI use known information from the model by prompting for [Kim Kardashian|Koh_KimKardashian] or [Kim Kardashian:Koh_KimKardashian:0.8]. This allows the AI more creativity and it will get more varied outputs, it's worth trying.

If you enjoy my creations and want to support me or have a face you'd like to commission, consider supporting me on Ko-Fi or Buy Me A Coffee :)

items.name: Anime Toilet Scene Concept
items.description:
Anime Toilet Scene Concept

This is my first uploaded LoRA. It is intended to assist in creating images depicting the niche trope of walking in on a cute girl while she's using the bathroom, often resulting in an exciting or embarrassing encounter.

It was trained on approximately 500 curated images of varying quality with manual tag cleanup against the base NAI model. While many checkpoints can technically depict this, they often miss the nuance of its underlying appeal, so this LoRA may help.

How to Use

The LoRA should play nice with other style-based and character-based LoRAs, so you can use it to make images depicting your favorite characters in this situation (and please to do!).

(A manually edited image for demonstration of compatibility with character LoRAs, https://civitai.com/models/19001/rias-gremory-high-school-dd)

In the first run of training, I only ran a single repeat on the dataset, so it can often require the LoRA and associated keywords to be set to very high influence in order to sufficiently bias the output. It often requires a lot of fiddling to get right, but with enough effort, you can get some very good results.

I was also hoping some of the newly introduced tags such 'panties above knees' and 'panties below knees' would allow a strong degree of specificity when it came to depicting this, but unfortunately this does not seem to work, so I would stick to the 'pants pull' or 'panty pull' tags and simply hope for the best, perhaps inpainting when it fails.

This LoRA is not specifically trained at depicting anything more explicit than simply showing characters using the bathroom, so it should be relatively tame, though will sometimes generate nudity.

Future Versions

Since this is an early attempt at training something like this, I would like to do more with this idea in the future. Some ideas I have include a larger dataset, more repeats, more curation, and possibly more manual cleanup supplemented with high quality synthetic data. Any feedback and advice would be highly welcome~!

✔️ANIME STYLE

***USE CLIP SKIP 2 FOR THIS MODEL! YOU CAN DO CLIP SKIP 1 AS WELL BUT 2 IS BEST!***

READ ME! THERE IS INFO ON HOW YOU CAN GET THE MOST OUT OF THIS MODEL!

There is a full & pruned version of this model available. This is a complex merge so even the pruned version is large as well.


There is no embedded VAE but it was designed to be used with this:


☞ vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.ckpt


I recommend using the following negatives:


EasyNegative (The all around catch all. Always good in a bind)
badhandv4_anime (absolutely your go to neg for anime hands)
bad-hands-5 (good for the more realistic images but will not work amazingly for anime)
bad-artist \ bad-artist-anime (I’ve had good and bad luck)
bad_prompt \ bad_prompt_version2 (works very good sometimes)
(I typically use (bad-hands-5) & (bandhandv4_anime) at the same time to cover more bases)


*** Note: that the example images are provided as a basis of reference and raw output. In most cases untouched other than mild inpainting for the eyes or face in a few examples. *** THESE SHOULD BE EASILY REPRODUCIBLE RESULTS! IF YOU HAVE QUESTIONS PLEASE ASK 🗪


Note: There is a full & pruned version of this model available. This is a complex merge so even the pruned is also large as well.


Here are some optimal example settings for you to start with, but please keep in mind YMMV!


Steps 20-30 = Sweet Spot / 15-150
Sampler DPM++ 2M Karras, DPM++ SDE Karras, Euler A, DDIM,
CFG scale 4-9.5 = Sweet Spot / 3-20
Size 512x768, 768x512, 640x840, 840x640, 600x896, 896x600, (any size)
Clip skip 2
Hires Fix Enabled
Upscale by 1.5-2
Hires Steps Equal to Half or Exact amount of Steps or higher
Upscaler Remacri Upscaler, Lollypop Upscaler, 4x_NMKD_DigArt_10k|

_________________________________ (Older Info from version 1.5) _________________________________

A handpicked and curated merge of the best of the best in waifu’s, anime, 2D, and of course, fantasy environments, characters & creature designs. It doesn’t do everything but what it can do off the bat is a pretty damned amazing images in anime styles 2 - 2.5D quite effectively. 🎨

Specializes in illustrated, semi-realistic, painterly, subjective reality and a 2.5d aesthetic with semi real to real backgrounds. Backgrounds that look like high quality anime or 3d rendered, game backgrounds.

It does styles and illustration, and artists based prompts pretty damned well and adapts to most LORAS with ease, it DEFINITELY leans a bit towards nudity / NSFW and also more towards younger looking girls. (Look I didn’t plan this… the merges just made it that way.) I suggest a (((kids))), (((child))), (Young:1.5-2.0) in your negative and a (mature adult:1.5-2.0) in your positive.

However… it will also work with Clip Skip 1 better for prompts that are going after a specific art or artists styles. (Unsure if this is directly affected by LORA’s will have to test more) Example:

Notice that the art & artist style of the prompt comes out more in 1 and 2 has more of the industrial / cyber aspects. Play with it and see what works best for you.

SHOW ME WHAT YOU MAKE WITH THIS!! 😉

Here are some example image comparisons with some of the most common / top anime oriented models and also my previous model Dungeons N Waifu’s v2.2:

I was asked recently how to get higher quality images like the examples and about blurred eyes and faces:


Blurred eyes, or sometimes warped faces are not that uncommon in SD and sometimes require an inpaint to pull off. Most of my examples are not inpainted. But a few are.


First off when you run txt2img ALWAYS use HIRES FIX!


latent (nearest or exact) upscale / denoise 0.4-0.7 (Complete variable - depends on the type and complexity of the image. YMMV!)


Upscale by 1.5-2 but no more than that.

This will get you a pretty good base image to work with.


Afterwards… You can always send your txt2img picture to inpaint on the bottom right under the result area > select the face or eyes > lower the denoise strength to 0.5-0.57. > make sure your seed is set to random.

masked content = fill / inpaint area = whole picture ====== for faces

masked content = fill / inpaint area = only masked ====== for eyes


With “whole picture” selected for larger inpaint target aka faces (or hands) you may need the denoise to be lower to pick up more of the original image. 0.53-0.56


Now with “only masked” and a smaller target like eyes you get a little more freedom so your denoise can be 0.54-0.57


Run a batch of 4-5 (or more) for the faces… go through pick the best one… if you’re lucky you got the eyes and face in one go… if not you may need to choose the best face… send back to inpaint again… select just the eyes… and rerun a new batch (changing it to only masked and the settings described above for eyes.)


Finally when you get it all together send to extras:

Resize to 1.5-2

Upscale 1= Nearest
Upscale 2= R-ESERGAN 2x or 4x
But google & get yourself Remacri Upscaler and Lollypop Upscaler
4x_NMKD_Superscale-SP_178000_G


Upscaler 2 is what will get you there. If you want super sharp / realism images you choose NMKD


You want a good all around upscaler that can do nearly any subject you choose Remacri

If you’re working on toons, anime, animated, cell shaded you choose Lollypop

Each of these is unique and so is their outputs if you want to compare simply change the pull down and run off the various types and contrast / compare the finished results.

For the more advanced upscale: Get yourself Ultimate SD Upscale
(click the link for a basic tutorial on how to get it and how to use it.)

Good Luck & Have Fun!

items.name: NSFW aodai
items.description:
For those who can't see more than 2 sample images: Go to your account settings and toggle adult contents off and on again.

This is the nsfw lora version of the aodai, or Vietnamese dress.

The difference between this lora and the other aodai models/embeddings out there is that this one has been trained exclusively with over 100 lewd aodai images. You will find these dresses to be a bit more transparent with the occasional visible nipples, or maybe a missing pair of pants. Who knows?

Another point which drove me into making this lora is that it's hard to get the bottom half of the dress right if your character doesn't stand upright. Half of the time they look like they're wearing the bottom of a swim suit. This lora does a decent job to represent the dress on different postures too. Keyword: a decent job, it's not perfect. I don't think it can ever be perfect. Getting the AI to reliably pick on the two splits is looking like an impossible task to me at this point.

It'll work on some custom character loras to a certain extend. I'm planning to fine-tune this lora to reduce artifacts on the dress in the near future. Also works with latex texture for those of you who are fancy about giving it a go.

V2 update:

Not sure if I can call this version definitely better than V1 but here are some note-worthy things about V2:

  • Works best around 0.7 - 0.9 weight. Personally I use 0.7 for all of the sample images. Make sure that you have <lora:aodaimong_v2:x>, ((y aodaimong)) as your prompt, with x being the weight and y the color. Add "latex" to y to get latex texturing on your dress. By default with no y it's a white dress.

  • This version distinguishes hair and dress colors much better than V1. In V1, 9 out of 10 times you'll get the same dress color as your hair if you choose to specify what the character's hair color is. That is no longer the case in V2.

  • Fixes some texture issues. I did my best to smooth out the dress so hopefully you won't see as much weird textures as in V1.

  • Works more consistently with other poses.

  • Pants are a lot rarer now. It's virtually impossible to have the pants generated consistently during my testing so I decided to reduce the frequency of it as a result.

  • Added a few more prompts to control a few parameters and provide a more consistent set of images in general. I.e: You have more control of what you want your character to do/look like now instead of leaving it to the randomness of the AI. See below.

  • Added a prompt to consistently showing no bra on your character: khongbra.

  • Added some poses. Try using these prompts: posing for photo, holding a cloth.

  • Latex texture works fairly consistent now. With all colors but white that is.

  • Overall it's an improvement based on what I wanted to do. Feel free to go back and forth between the two versions depending on your needs.

Credit

I'd like to credit the following creators for I've been using their characters a lot during my testing:

  • Nyaa and their virtual girls series. Absolutely my favorite.

  • asian_ai and their Vyvan Le character model. Who else is better to model these dresses if not a Viet girl herself?

  • lamlnq and their aodai checkpoint. Check them out too, gave me the inspiration to make this lora.

I personally think V2 is going to be the final version of this lora, at least for now. I ran out of new images to add to the dataset and training the AI any further will just end up overcooking it. I got an idea for V3 so currently working on it. No promise it'll ever be done though, very few sample size right now.

Please do post what you are able to make using this lora, I love seeing them.

⚠️你需要自行承担传播生成数据所产生的风险与责任。

WTF?

YaoZhi is an original character by the artist FKEY, a beautiful oriental Taoist nun with the ability to manipulate corpses, this LORA focuses on attempting to reproduce the physical characteristics of this character, including elements of headdress, hair, costume, etc., and is suitable for depicting a single female character.

It does not reproduce the art style of the artist FKEY.

Like this girl? Go support FKEY

For ver 1.5

" yaozhi\(fkey\), yaozhi\(china_cloth\), "

  • Grey pupils: try adding "grey_eyes"

Weights

items.description:
这是我训练的第二个Lora模型。这个角色是Re：creator的席利乌斯，仅仅出场一集她后就被阿尔泰尔占据了身体。

这个Lora模型是基于final-prune.ckpt（【旧短哈希1d4a34af】新短哈希22fa233c2d），使用了768x768的数据集进行训练。

通常情况下不需要Trigger Words就能触发该Lora，但是为了更好的效果，还是推荐加上sirius，1girl，solo这些Trigger Words。

推荐使用0.6-0.8的权重，除了提到的触发词以外，其他的人物特征是不必要提到的，但如果你想要更好的效果，也可以添加，因为一些细节（比如人物的袖章，或者护手可能会在生成时丢失）。

如果人物无法生成你想要的动作，请增加动作的权重或者降低Lora的权重。

如果生成的人物图像面部不佳，推荐您勾选高清修复。

这个模型可以生成nsfw的图片。

测试了kotosmix以及AbyssOrangeMix2，AbyssOrangeMix3，以及anyhentai和Grapefruit，其中AbyssOrangeMix的模型生成的人物图像面部，可能会出现一些问题。

如果可以的话，请在评论区留言以告知我这个Lora在其他的模型上是否好用，谢谢。

英语是用Google翻译的，如果有造成误解之处非常抱歉。

This is the second LORA model I trained. This role is Re: Creator's Sirius, after just one episode, she was occupied by Altair.

This LoRa model is based on Final-Prone.ckpt ([Old Short Hash 1D4A34AF] New Short Hash 22FA233C2D), which uses a dataset of 768x768 for training.

Usually, the TRIGGGER WORDS is required to trigger the LoRa, but for better results, it is recommended to add Sirius, 1Girl, SOLO these Trigger Words.

It is recommended to use the weight of 0.6-0.8. Except for the triggers mentioned, other character characteristics are not necessary to mention, but if you want a better effect, you can also add it, because some details (such as the character's sleeve, Or the handle may be lost during generation).

If the character cannot generate the action you want, please increase the weight of the action or reduce the weight of LORA.

If the character's image is not good, it is recommended to check the high -definition repair.

This model can generate NSFW pictures.

Test Kotosmix and ABYSSORANGEMIX2, ABYSORANGEMIX3, and Anyhentai and Grapefruit, where the character image of the character generated by ABYSSARANGEMIX may have some problems.

If possible, please leave a message in the comment area to let me know if this Lora works well on other models, thank you.

English is translated with Google, which is very sorry for misunderstanding.

items.description:
Gretel Grant Gomez from 'hamster and gretel'

To be honest, Gretel character design is quite difficult to be learned, so you have to use inpaint feature a lot.

(Quite difficult to make great pictures only using prompts)

Model : abyssorangemix2

Strength recommendation : 0.4 ~ 0.9

items.name: Star wars Imperial navy trooper uniform
items.description:
Probably my last entry in the funny helmet category.

You should add "with helmet on" in the propmt to get best results.

It is recommended to set the background in the prompt. It also helps when you add black before the uniform, to get the best color.
